  "texts": [
    "For clarity, here we illustrate with MNIST dataset.",
    "The number of types/classes of images (referred to as m in this article) in the MNIST dataset is 10.",
    "The images are compressed in a *.idx3-ubyte file that can be opened with MATLAB; each of them comes in grayscale and with a resolution of 28×28 pixels.",
    "In Python, the MNIST images can be found embedded in a library named Keras.",
    "The training images are used to let the ANN understand the characteristic features of each pattern (i.e., the numbers), and the testing images are presented to the ANN (after training) to be classified."
  ],
